ownedComment.body: A concrete Kpi subclass should use appropriate concrete KpiDetails. The generic KpiDetails is concrete and may be used where the details consist only of cost.
There should be at most one Kpi element of each concrete type

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Namespace.definition: Package with constructs to describe results of evaluation of traffic management responses

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: Evaluation results for one response measure, for the metric of air quality.
Evaluation results relating to one response measure, for the metric of air quality, representing either the scenario that the measure is in effect or the scenario that it is not in effect.
The evaluation results for one response measure, for the metric of delay.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: Ignoring congestion effects, the total extra time taken by vehicles due to the response measure.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: Evaluation results relating to one response measure, for the metric of delay, representing either the scenario that the measure is in effect or the scenario that it is not in effect.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: The total extra time (compared with freely flowing conditions) taken by vehicles in this scenario

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: The evaluation results for one response measure for one kind of metric

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Relation.definition: Evaluation results for the scenario that the response measure is in effect
Evaluation results for the scenario that the response measure is not in effect

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: Evaluation results relating to one response measure, for a single scenario: either the scenario that the measure is in effect or the scenario that it is not in effect.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: The total of monetized costs assigned for this particular metric for a given response and scenario

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: The evaluation results for one response measure.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: Expected change in traffic demand caused by this measure while it is active. For example, for a diversion this quantity will divert from the original route to the alternative route while the diversion is active.
Identifies the measure for which these results apply.
The contribution to utility made by the measure, expressed as a money value. A positive value means a benefit, a negative value means a cost.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Relation.definition: The evaluation results for response measures that are included in the set that produced the best combined utility. If all combinations of measures have been evaluated to be worse than making no response, this will be empty.
The evaluation results for response measures that are not included in the set that produced the best combined utility – i.e. the responses which, if added to the best set, would make things worse.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: Details of emissions of pollutants and atmospheric pollution levels

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: The total quantity of emissions of the specified pollutant

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: The results of an evaluation of potential traffic management plans

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Attribute.definition: The best result (most savings, or least costs) from evaluated permutations of responses. This is expressed as a money value in units of Euros. A positive value means a benefit, a negative value means a cost.
Identifies the service that produced these evaluation results.

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Package.definition: Classes for expressing results of evaluation of traffic management plans

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Datatype.definition: Identical semantics to the type in Parking which should be promoted to Common
A value of weight expressed in units of kilograms
An absolute value (not a rate) of traffic delay in vehicle hours

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: Publication of situations with evaluation results for operator actions representing potential or running traffic management plans

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2ModelRoot.definition: Publication of situations with evaluation results for operator actions representing potential or running traffic management plans

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Package.definition: Constructs for publishing situations with evaluation results for operator actions representing potential or running traffic management plans

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Class.definition: Publication of results of evaluation of potential traffic management plans

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2ModelRoot.definition: Publication of results of evaluation of potential traffic management plans

UML_Profile_for_DATEX_II:D2Package.definition: Constructs for publishing results of evaluation of potential traffic management plans
